{"TopicId":223647,"ForumId":144,"TopicTitle":"Orbital Decay Fix does not work during and after Kerbal EVA if vessel is currently experiencing a Landed State Bug","CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-11T23:15:47Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-11T23:15:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.1 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0win10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0i710700k | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0rtx2060 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32gb\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe true Herobrine of KSP2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSteps:\u003Cbr\u003E\n1. Load attached save.\u003Cbr\u003E\n2. Observe.\u003Cbr\u003E\n2.5 If doesn\u0027t happen, repeat: go on EVA, return to ship, observe\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI suppose it\u0027s worth mentioning that the ship had no trajectory in map view after liftoff. This usually gets fixed after reload, so I suppose better steps are as follows: Land anything on Dres. Get out, plant a flag, take it down, return to ship, liftoff, repeat step 2.5 making sure no trajectory is present. No decay present while using jetpack.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVideo Evidence:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cvideo class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 controls=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.global.core.embeddedvideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Csource type=\u0022video/mp4\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_02/Ksp2X64.Exe202402.11-23552410Dvr.mp4.1c5491a2deaa9324e289f31a6c81e816.mp4\u0022\u003E\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022mp4\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221345\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/attachment.php?id=1345\u0026amp;key=246fb343630d153ca6bab245149e0184\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EKsp2 X64.Exe2024 02.11-23 55 24 10 Dvr.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/video\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESave file:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221347\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/attachment.php?id=1347\u0026amp;key=e4f35f7455b09c06979fb70add86ff9f\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022json\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Edec.json\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-02-12T19:49:58Z\u0022 title=\u002202/12/2024 07:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Feb 12\u0022\u003EFebruary 12\u003C/time\u003E by Spicat\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-12T00:31:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI highly believe this is because of the landed state bug (not fixable by a reload):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022226862\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2074635556\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/221540-incorrect-landed-status-while-in-orbit-causes-trajectory-to-disappear-in-map-view?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:377px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe game think the craft is landed and that\u0027s maybe why the orbital decay fix is not applied to it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly a theory obviously because you didn\u0027t attach the save file to your bug report. (You can resend a bug report with just the save and the link to this bug report and we\u0027ll put the save here)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-12T00:33:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224366026\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022223647\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221707697898\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022228085\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spicat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Spicat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly a theory obviously because you didn\u0027t attach the save file to your bug report. (You can resend a bug report with just the save and the link to this bug report and we\u0027ll put the save here)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know, I forgot and realized after \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:ph34r:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_ph34r.png\u0022 title=\u0022:ph34r:\u0022\u003E. Will do (tomorrow)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-12T19:50:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/150811-the-aziz/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150811\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/150811-the-aziz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u00